,Recommended,223510,1449182,"Posted: 1 December, 2012",all,Xevo,"I was very impressed with this game overall. It starts out pretty rough at least partly by design, as being thrown into an unfamiliar setting and being so physically weak that you can barely move around and get easily lost are all part of the character. However, as you play the game you will learn how to get around more easily with the cartography mechanics, creating the right drugs to get you out of tough situations, and just as a result of internalizing the game's systems. Each time you create a shot that returns some of your physical abiltiies to normal the regular paths become easier to traverse and more difficult places become reachable. By the end of the game, you can get around so easily that it's hard to remember how rough it was at the beginning. Overall, the experience is very satisfying and I throughly recommend the game to anyone with the patience to get through the slower and tougher parts early on."
76561197974088172,Recommended,223510,11933561,"Posted: 31 August, 2014",all,father nurgle,"Miasmata is a really fun exploration game set in a beautiful world.  I ended up mapping the whole mainland during my playthrough.  Even after many hours and quite a few encounters, the sound signalling the approach of the creature was enough to make me start running madly across the map, usually resulting in disaster.  A few of the achievements seem to be broken, best to check online before aiming for them.  When creating the cure, make sure you actually pick up the test tubes for each part!  The objectives tick off even if you don't which is a bit confusing.  I ended up having to make them all a second time so I could complete the game."
