76561198002406091,Not Recommended,223510,9649758,"Posted: 27 March, 2014",all,Gorfinhofin,"In light of recent epiphanies I have had regarding my dislike of this game I have come up with a new, conciser review, but will keep the old one for... posterity or whatever.New Version:This game is a pioneer of the genre of early-access survival games, from before early-access even existed. Games like these feature a few neat gimmicks, a loosely established goal, and a veneer of realism, but are plagued by bugs and shoddy mechanics that are doomed to never be fixed. Today these games sit in the early-access section getting trivial updates every month or so until suddenly the developers get bored or realize that nobody is buying their game anymore and they give up. The game is left unfinished and forgotten.Miasmata gives the impression of being one of these forgotten end-products, except someone accidentally gave it a full release.Old Version:I was mildly enjoying this game until I accidentally strayed from the exact path the game wanted me to follow and I became hopelessly lost, unable to chart anything on my map, because obviously you can't map anything without a reference that is already on your map! You can't like start a new map and combine it with your old one later or something! That would be silly!Other assorted problems:The flame of the lighter has a faint green square around it where transparency is supposed to be.Trees produce an unnatural aura of darkness.Night is pitch black and if you aren't near a bed you basically have to stand around for 15 minutes until the sun rises.Falling over gives you a debilitating illness. (SO REALISTIC)Your character seems to think slopes are about twice as steep as they actually are.The monster is really dumb and it's hard to tell if you can even interact with it because its behavior makes no sense.I think there's some other glitchy stuff but I don't remember. I last played this game like over a year ago.Good things:The interface with the journal and the water bottle and medicine and stuff is pretty cool.Collecting flowers and mushrooms and making stuff is pretty cool I guess.The concept of the map making is pretty cool.That's about it."
