,Not Recommended,223510,284667,"Posted: 21 May, 2013",all,McFrugal,"This is a bad game, don't buy it.Your character controls like a drunk, stumbling all over the place and incapable of ascending a gentle slope at faster than crawling pace.  The game crashes when leaving the ESC menu.  There are a ton of cases where the wrong models are used during plant analysis.  The achievements are glitched to hell.You are in more danger of dying from tumbling down perfectly climbable inclines than you are of getting killed by the 'creature'.  Speaking of the creature, I met it once after playing for a couple hours.  You get a warning that it's nearby via a loud heartbeat.  There's no indication of what direction it's in, and if you see it out of cover it will see you.  However it doesn't really move very fast so if you just run away you're fine.  Despite what the store page says, it doesn't really track you- it just randomly spawns near you.  So, just run in practically any direction and you're fine until it randomly spawns near you again.  Pointless.  Oh and if it hits you, you die instantly.The landmark system sounds clever except for the fact that trees and inclines seem to be placed specifically so that you can't see landmarks most of the time.  Also there seem to be no sanity checks involved.  You can walk like 10 feet for a second triangulation to verify where distant landmarks are, and can use landmarks that are in line with you to verify your own position.  There's no minimum angle between landmarks or minimum distance between triangulations.Health is represented solely by how sick you are.  So, falling down a cliff gives you a fever, rather than bruises.  There's food on the island but you can't eat any of it because it's all half-rotten fruit.  You can supposedly drink from any non-saltwater source, but I already found a river that I couldn't drink from.This game is a MESS."
