,Recommended,223510,9919614,"Posted: 24 April, 2014",all,adrianmarshall167,"Miasmata is a game that redefines what you might picture as a game. It's almost not a game, in some ways; the punishing sicknesses you can get wandering around the island, the analysis of different flora to cure the aforementioned afflictions, and the use of your surroundings and triangulation to determine your position on the map...all of these things are something a person would do in the given circumstances. As a huge fan of first person games, I really enjoy the fact that the arms and hands are put to realistic use as well, and how immersive and well thought out the environment is. It surprises me still to imagine two people working on something of this scope. It has its little quirks, and some of the kinks in the fabric haven't quite been worked out just yet, but if you're looking for something that isn't your run of the mill first person shooter or puzzler, this game is definitely worth checking out."
