76561198127832826,Recommended,223510,14434462,"Posted: 11 February, 2015",all,Hydra238,"I really enjoyed this game, it took me 18 hours to make the cure and I am even somewhat sad that this journey is nearly over and I rarely get such a feeling when I finished a video game. In any case the game is a unique experience AND a niche game, so its not for everyone plus it has its faults (clipping issues, mapping can be tedious especially in the beginning and some objects like tends just vanish if they are farther away but can still be used as a point for triangulation if you know where they are, some graphics and textures don't look like they belong in because the rest of the environment is so well made and looks really beautiful) but those are only minor issues and didn't spoil my enjoyment in any serious way.Miasmata lives from its immersive atmosphere when I came home from a trip I made my medicine, studied my journal and map and planed the next tour for tomorrow before I sat down on the edge off a cliff and watched the sunset or the cloudburst over the sea and just enjoyed the world around me.The game for me like for some others was a ""slow starter"", I didn't really like the first 1-2 hours very much, maybe because I already knew the beginning from lets plays or because I felt so lost without clear cut instructions other than to make the cure and no way to tell were the ♥♥♥♥ I am right now, but as time flew by and I made progress I got slowly sucked into the world of Miasmata. Music plays sparingly but its very soothing and fitting in such situations when you just barely escaped the creature and reached a new safe haven or watch the sun go down from your shack before taking some well earned rest.The creature while not particularly smart or scary looking definitely gave me some memorable moments and is really the last thing you want to bump into when you spend your last 15 min mapping and trying to reach an outpost before night sets in. One day I ventured out found two new plants, got a lot of mapping done and forgot about the time so I didn't make it back to my base before nightfall. I got tired of waiting and my water was running out so I decided I will just try to slowly stumble forward through the darkness when suddenly I hear my heart beat. I turned around running as fast as I can before falling down a ridge landing in some bushes. Instinctively I ducked down and in the next moment the silhouette of the creature appeared on the ridge of the hill wandering around before running off.Needless to say I spend the rest of the night cowering in fetal position under my bush praying that Milo doesn't come back. I lost my plants but I survived that night, without water and a fever I dragged myself to a near outpost in the next morning and from that moment on I made sure to always make it home in time. Thats just one example, I had a few more thrilling moments but I will keep those to myself. And just to give you an idea I met the beast around 10-15 times in my 18h of playtime and that was just the right amount to keep it somewhat special.After playing it 76/100 as a neutral rating seems about right when you consider all the minor flaws it has and that it could have been even better with a bit more polish, but my personal rating would be closer to a 90/100 and I would definitely buy it again even at full price."
