76561197969828341,Recommended,223510,27156002,"Posted: 24 November, 2016",all,afxdub,"First, this game will not be for everyone.  It's a horror/suspense game with FPS type controls.  The main driver throughout the game is that you suffer from fevers.  To combat these fevers, you must craft medicine from plants you collect on the island.  Your in game character is no superman.  He has liminted stamina and too much strenuous activity will bring on a fever which could result in death.Added to that you have the constant threat of the island monster.  Plus, you start out with no map.  You must create it using topography and triangulation.  It's a really neat system that I've haven't seen used in any other game.  As you play, you gradually map out the entire island.Overally, I loved this game.  The pace, the constant threat of fevers and monsters, and the general weakness of the in-game character made the whole experience suspenseful and tense."
76561197971663594,Recommended,223510,531257,"Posted: 26 March, 2013",all,Draksis,"This game was recommended to by a forum friend, and at first I was very sceptical. Wow did this game surprise: This game has got to be the most incredible non-violent game I have ever played. To survive you must find the right plants to make pills and tonics for various purposes, from keeping the symptoms of the Plague away, to an extra boost to your system to sprint or swim for longer. All the while in fear of being found by a mysterious creature.There is something about quietly hunting for glowing algae at night one minute, and sprinting full pace down a narrow jungle path with only your burning bunch of twigs as your light the next!...."
76561198003086122,Recommended,223510,2151289,"Posted: 17 March, 2013",all,DMK Gman,"This is not an action game: there is no combat although there is an animal on the island which will kill you if you fail to hide from it.This is a game of exploration: you are stranded on an island, suffering from a plague.  The cure is on this Island although those that made it are all dead.  You explore the island, mapping it as you go, searching for the plants required to create the cure (as well as the scientists notes with regards as to which plants you actually require).  In your diseased state you are weak.  A slight fall, dehydration or lack of sleep will lead to a fever...left untreated the fever will kill you.  You can use various plants around the island to synthesise drugs to combat the fever or to increase your strenght, endurance and awareness.In this game it is the environment which is your enemy: the island is a mountainous, jungle environment full of steap slopes: in Miasmata your body has momentum and navigating all of those hills becomes a matter of life or death.  You will slide, trip and fall but it all feels very natural.I loved this game: the island setting is well realised...the sounds of the environment are very well done, while the lighting is fantastic.The game was made by two people, with an engine they built specifically for the purpose.  There are rough patches to the graphics but I can honestly say that I never noticed them unless I went looking for them.I highly recommend it, but it may not be to everyone's taste."
