,Recommended,223510,17213566,"Posted: 24 July, 2015",all,Alex Ros,"One of the most innovative games outhere. Some people may consider it boring, cause practically everything you do is roaming around and looking for flowers, mushrooms. At the same time you do not have any map and you have to travel very carefully and have to use triangulation technique just to know where you are. Without triangulation usage you will be lost really fast and... eaten. Yes. There's a creature roaming around too. What is more interesting is that this creature is unscripted. It means you can meet it right at the first day. Vice versa you can meet your enemy on day 10 for example. Nevertheless you will meet it eventually, because most of times it's roaming around the most important rare ingridients (flowers-mushrooms). Another one enemy is your own sickness, physical not mental. You're sick, so you have to make hand-made pills regularly. There's also a dehydration, but no starvation for some unknown reasons. Anyway dehydration is not a problem at all, nothing would change without this lively but useless detail. And that's almost everything I can say about game mechanics. The way you can get lost and be frightened is the only one outstanding feature; really big open world created believable and full of points of interest for explorers.As for the story it's all hidden in notes and some photographs. No voices, no scenes, no characters alive. You are all alone (if not to mention the creature). Story is nice, mysterious and a bit detectivish. And by the way it's crucial to collect story notes, otherwise looking for ingridiends will become a pain in the a$$. You do can collect plants blindly, but that's really hard.I would recommend that game to anyone who is not afraid to try something new and unique. It's not expensive, so I really recommend to give it a try."
