76561198077949920,Recommended,223510,35252427,Posted: 27 September,all,Jemmy,"I very highly recommend this game...to a certain type of person. It's really about what type of game you like to play. If you're not sure, buy it on sale and give it a chance!I liked it because:- There is no combat.- You're mostly just exploring a beautiful island (in immersive first-person view).- The mapping technique was unique and challenging.- The character movements are realistic of someone who is sick: you're a little sluggish and it's easy to get hurt. (Once I actually said ""Whew!"" out loud after climbing up a steep hill. This was a big part of the immersion for me.)- Plot was interesting and drove me forward. Though it's not in your face - you have to look for it.- It's fun to replay once you know what's going on. (1st playthrough took me about 20 hours; 2nd playthrough I attempted a speedrun in about 2 hours.)You may NOT like it because:- There is no combat.- You're mostly just exploring a beautiful island.- Mapping technique is a little hard to learn (but once you ""get"" it, it's fine).- Character movements can be clunky.- You have to search for notes and clues to learn the story.P.S. I think some of the achievements might be bugged, but I can forgive that. Maybe you can't."
